---
title: One-Pan Ginger Beef Lettuce Wraps With Zucchini, Gochujang Sauce & Pickled Carrots
description: “Hot beef, cold lettuce, can’t lose!” That’s what we think the rallying cry should’ve been on that high school football drama. This winning combo takes a page from the Korean barbecue playbook. Here, we cook ground beef and zucchini in a savory sauce that gets sweet heat from gochujang, a Korean chili paste. Crisp romaine leaves cradle the gingery beef filling along with tangy pickled carrots. This is definitely a meal that’ll have you cheering for the home (cooking) team!
